TITLE: 'I'm outraged:' Women react to Roe v. Wade ruling outside of Supreme Court
SUMMARY: Following the decision, supporters and opponents of the decision gathered outside the nation's highest court.

TITLE: Supreme Court abortion ruling is 'catastrophic,' liberal justices write in furious dissent
SUMMARY: The majority overruled Roe and Casey "because it has always despised them," wrote Justices Stephen Breyer, Sonia Sotomayor and Elena Kagan in a joint dissent.

TITLE: Trump takes credit for end of Roe v. Wade after his 3 Supreme Court justice picks vote to void abortion rights
SUMMARY: Trump nominated three of the Supreme Court justices who voted to overturn Roe v. Wade, the 1973 case that affirmed a constitutional right to abortion.

TITLE: Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas says gay rights, contraception rulings should be reconsidered after Roe is overturned
SUMMARY: Abortion no longer is a federal right with Roe v. Wade overturned. Supreme Court Justice Thomas now is eyeing cases related to gay rights and birth control.

SUMMARY: Congress passed the most significant gun bill in decades, with steps to limit ownership for young buyers and domestic violence offenders.

SUMMARY: Garland said DOJ "strongly disagrees" with the court's ruling and will "work tirelessly to protect and advance reproductive freedom."

SUMMARY: The Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade, the landmark abortion rights decision, on Friday morning.

TITLE: Supreme Court overturns Roe v. Wade, ending 50 years of federal abortion rights
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court has overturned Roe v. Wade, the landmark ruling that enshrined abortion as a constitutional right in the U.S. for almost half a century.

SUMMARY: Jeffrey Clark, whom Donald Trump planned to install as acting attorney general, will be discussed by the committee investigating the Jan. 6 Capitol riot.

SUMMARY: The Supreme Court ruling is a victory for Second Amendment advocates, who opposed the New York law restricting concealed carry gun licenses.

SUMMARY: President Joe Biden called for a federal gas tax holiday as people across the U.S. deal with spiking prices.

SUMMARY: The U.S. has provided $5.6 billion in weapons to Ukraine since Russia invaded in late February.

SUMMARY: Assange is wanted in the U.S. over the publication of hundreds of thousands of classified military documents and diplomatic cables.

SUMMARY: Subpoenas were issued seeking information about Trump's former personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani and another Trump lawyer, John Eastman, The Times reported.

TITLE: Dr. Anthony Fauci tests positive for Covid, is having mild symptoms
SUMMARY: Dr. Anthony Fauci has not been in recent close contact with President Joe Biden. Fauci is the U.S. government's leader in coronavirus pandemic response.
